{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"227af8db-f728-4d00-b91c-6d12d559fcac","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory, so here's general guidance for the switch:\n\n### Changes needed for NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. Register your package on nuget.org**\n- Go to nuget.org → your package → **Manage** → **Publishing policies**\n- Add a **Trusted Publisher** entry, specifying your GitHub repo, branch/tag pattern, and optionally the workflow filename and environment\n\n**2. Update your workflow**\n\nAdd `id-token: write` permission and remove the API key:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write  # Required for OIDC\n      contents: read\n    # Optional: lock to a GitHub Environment matching your nuget.org config\n    # environment: nuget-publish\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release -o ./nupkgs\n\n      - name: Publish to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push ./nupkgs/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n        # No --api-key needed — the OIDC token is used automatically\n```\n\n**3. Key differences from your current setup**\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC token (automatic) |\n| `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | No `--api-key` flag needed |\n| No special permissions | `id-token: write` required |\n\n**4. Remove** the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once verified.\n\n> **Note:** `dotnet nuget push` supports OIDC natively starting with .NET SDK 9+. If you're on an older SDK, you may need to manually obtain and pass the token — check the [NuGet docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/nuget/nuget-org/publish-a-package#publish-with-trusted-publishers) for details.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"74fb2411-934c-4bee-931e-d5bd07fc0729","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no workflow files in the current directory. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to trusted publishing (OIDC). Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":585,"requestId":"E425:285BD2:6D9795A:75E2D23:6A03CD1E"},"id":"648706d1-ef3e-4fec-b38e-f02ace584568","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:00:27.840Z","parentId":"d77b8c9f-476a-4de6-aa4e-9cbb497c64a8"}
